        "title": "hiPet",
        "template": "static-project",
        "image": "/images/portfolio/stacked-fullwidth/ima-4.jpg",
        "meta": [
            "<strong>Client:</strong> Original idea&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Year:</strong> 2014 / 2016&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Category:</strong> Innovation Venture · Interface Design"
        ],
        "contentHtml": `
            <p class="summary-text">
            hiPet was born from a simple but urgent real-life problem. While exploring mechanisms to remotely open and close doors via mobile, an unexpected call changed everything. A friend asked for a life-or-death favor: feeding their cat for two days. That moment sparked a new idea—what if caring for your pet could be managed from anywhere?
            </p>

            <p>
            hiPet is a smart pet feeder connected to a mobile app, designed to dispense food remotely and give pet owners peace of mind when they’re away. More than a device, hiPet became a bridge between pet lovers and technology, combining hardware, software, and intuitive interface design to create a seamless experience. This project explored how IoT, mobile interfaces, and emotional design could come together to solve everyday problems with simplicity and empathy.
            </p>
        `,
