        "template": "project",
        "image": "/images/portfolio/slider-single/villa-mascotas-1.jpg",
        
        "meta": [
        "<strong>Client:</strong> UNE&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Year:</strong> 2010&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Category:</strong> Game 3D&nbsp;&nbsp; Massively Multiplayer Online · Social Game"
        ],
        "gallery": [
            "/images/portfolio/slider-single/villa-mascotas-1.jpg",
            "/images/portfolio/slider-single/villa-mascotas-2.jpg",
            "/images/portfolio/slider-single/villa-mascotas-3.jpg",
            "/images/portfolio/slider-single/villa-mascotas-4.jpg"
        ],
        "contentHtml": `
            <p class="summary-text">
            Villa Mascotas was a 3D massively multiplayer social game designed as an open, shared world where players could interact, play, and grow together.
            </p>

            <p class="mar-top-30 mar-bot-30">
            The platform launched with 12 distinct scenarios, each part of a vibrant virtual environment populated by avatar-like characters. Players could chat in real time, participate in minigames, and earn points through various activities available worldwide, encouraging exploration and social interaction.<br><br>
            I was actively involved in the conceptualization and creation of the game world, contributing to the design of the environments, interactions, and overall experience. The goal was to build a playful and engaging ecosystem that felt alive and constantly active thanks to player presence.<br><br>
            As a massively multiplayer online game (MMO), Pet Village supported hundreds, potentially thousands, of players connected simultaneously to the same server, enabling large-scale shared experiences and reinforcing its identity as a social and community-driven virtual world.
            </p>
        `,
